This paper is about the CheckThat! Lab, which focuses on identifying and verifying claims in social media. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for tasks such as text classification, information retrieval, and fact-checking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for Task 3, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning and data mining techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the proposed methods, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
